Controllers are responsible for responding to requests from a web browser, mobile application or any other system capable of communicating with a server. Each route is mapped into the action and the action responds to requests. The controllers with modules are the main feature of the framework logic.

```plain
Initialization: Modules --> Packages --> Models --> Definitions --> Controllers
```

The controller __knows 3x types of routes__: _classic_, _websocket_ and _file route_.

- The classic route handles a classic requests into the dynamic content (view engine).
- The websocket route handles WebSockets connections.
- The file route handles static files.

---

__More informations__

- The controller is the plain JavaScript file with `.js` extension.
- The framework automatically loads the controller into the memory.
- All controllers are stored in `your-app/controllers/` directory.
- `exports.install` is executed automatically and one time.
- Views are loaded according to the controller name `your-app/views/your-controller-name/`.
- You can create unlimited count of controllers.
- The controller can be injected from the URL address, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/framework-install-controller).
- Routing supports routing according to the subdomains, [example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/routing-subdomain).
- The controller can communicate with the other controller.

